{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01FWUBgoZ92sfBvqpoEvkFzT","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Let me now compile a comprehensive report with all the information.\n\n## Coinflip Program Exploration Report\n\nI've thoroughly explored the coinflip program structure. Here's the complete breakdown:\n\n---\n\n### **1. DIRECTORY STRUCTURE**\n\n```\n/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/programs/coinflip/src/\n├── lib.rs\n├── state.rs\n├── error.rs\n└── instructions/\n    ├── mod.rs\n    ├── initialize_config.rs\n    ├── create_match.rs\n    ├── join_match.rs\n    ├── resolve_match.rs\n    ├── claim_payout.rs\n    ├── cancel_match.rs\n    ├── timeout_cancel.rs\n    └── force_close.rs\n```\n\n---\n\n### **2. STATE DEFINITIONS** (`src/state.rs`)\n\n**CoinflipConfig** (singleton PDA at `[b\"coinflip_config\"]`):\n- `authority`: Admin authority for config updates\n- `oracle_authority`: VRF callback signer (test keypair or MagicBlock)\n- `treasury`: Fee destination wallet\n- `bump`: PDA bump seed\n\n**CoinflipMatch** (PDA per creator at `[b\"match\", creator.key()]`):\n- `creator`: Match creator\n- `opponent`: Opponent (Pubkey::default() if empty)\n- `tier`: Tier index (0-5)\n- `entry_amount`: Entry amount in lamports (derived from tier)\n- `creator_side`: 0 = Heads, 1 = Tails\n- `phase`: Current phase (0=WAITING, 1=LOCKED, 2=SETTLED)\n- `result`: Winning side (0 or 1, only valid when settled)\n- `winner`: Winner's pubkey (Pubkey::default() until settled)\n- `claimed`: Whether payout claimed\n- `locked_at`: Unix timestamp when entered LOCKED phase\n- `bump`: PDA bump seed\n\n---\n\n### **3. PROGRAM ENTRY POINT** (`src/lib.rs`)\n\n**Program ID**: `H8Q2R1bUxzfUkV6WRRiZxYWwGfCr794AcnskWpsRQJf3`\n\n**8 Instructions**:\n1. `initialize_config(oracle_authority, treasury)` → InitializeConfig\n2. `create_match(tier, side)` → CreateMatch\n3. `join_match()` → JoinMatch\n4. `resolve_match(randomness: [u8; 32])` → ResolveMatch\n5. `claim_payout()` → ClaimPayout\n6. `cancel_match()` → CancelMatch\n7. `timeout_cancel()` → TimeoutCancel\n8. `force_close()` → ForceClose\n\n---\n\n### **4. ERROR CODES** (`src/error.rs`)\n\n| Code | Error | Message |\n|------|-------|---------|\n| 6100 | InvalidSide | Invalid side: must be 0 (Heads) or 1 (Tails) |\n| 6101 | InvalidTier | Invalid tier index |\n| 6102 | InvalidPhase | Match is not in the expected phase |\n| 6103 | InsufficientFunds | Insufficient funds for entry amount |\n| 6104 | CannotJoinOwnMatch | Creator cannot join their own match |\n| 6105 | UnauthorizedOracle | Only the oracle authority can resolve matches |\n| 6106 | AlreadyClaimed | Payout has already been claimed |\n| 6107 | NotWinner | Only the winner can claim the payout |\n| 6108 | CannotCancel | Match can only be cancelled in WAITING phase |\n| 6109 | VrfRequestFailed | VRF randomness request failed |\n| 6110 | LockTimeoutNotElapsed | Lock timeout has not elapsed yet (2 min) |\n| 6111 | UnauthorizedCaller | Only the creator or opponent can cancel |\n\n---\n\n### **5. INSTRUCTIONS DETAIL**\n\n#### **InitializeConfig** (`initialize_config.rs`)\n- **Requires**: Authority signer\n- **Creates**: Config PDA (singleton)\n- **Sets**: oracle_authority, treasury, authority, bump\n\n#### **CreateMatch** (`create_match.rs`)\n- **Requires**: Creator signer\n- **Creates**: Match PDA (one per creator)\n- **Validates**: Tier (0-5), Side (0 or 1)\n- **Action**: Transfers entry_amount to match escrow\n- **State**: phase=WAITING, opponent=default, claimed=false\n\n#### **JoinMatch** (`join_match.rs`) ⭐ **VRF Integration**\n- **Requires**: Opponent signer, Match in WAITING phase\n- **Validates**: Opponent ≠ Creator\n- **Action**: Transfers entry_amount to match escrow\n- **VRF Request**: Calls MagicBlock Ephemeral VRF via `create_request_randomness_ix()`\n  - Uses match_key as caller_seed for uniqueness\n  - Sets discriminator to resolve_match [73, 0, 15, 197, 178, 47, 21, 193]\n  - Passes config and match as callback account metas\n- **State Update**: phase=LOCKED, opponent set, locked_at=current_time\n- **Feature**: `mock-oracle` mode skips CPI (for bankrun tests)\n\n#### **ResolveMatch** (`resolve_match.rs`)\n- **Requires**: Oracle signer (must match config.oracle_authority)\n- **Input**: randomness: [u8; 32]\n- **Validates**: Match in LOCKED phase\n- **Logic**: \n  - result = randomness[0] % 2 (0 or 1)\n  - winner = if result == creator_side { creator } else { opponent }\n- **State Update**: phase=SETTLED, result, winner set\n\n#### **ClaimPayout** (`claim_payout.rs`)\n- **Requires**: Caller (either creator or opponent), match in SETTLED phase\n- **Validates**: Winner pubkey matches on-chain winner, prevents double-claim\n- **Pool**: entry_amount × 2\n- **Fee**: calculate_fee(pool) = 3% (300 bps)\n- **Payout**: pool - fee\n- **Actions**:\n  - Transfer payout to winner\n  - Transfer fee to treasury\n  - CPI to platform program to update player profiles (if exist)\n- **Cleanup**: Closes match account, refunds rent to creator\n\n#### **CancelMatch** (`cancel_match.rs`)\n- **Requires**: Creator signer\n- **Validates**: Match in WAITING phase only\n- **Action**: Closes account, returns all lamports (escrow + rent) to creator\n\n#### **TimeoutCancel** (`timeout_cancel.rs`)\n- **Requires**: Either creator or opponent signer\n- **Validates**: Match in LOCKED phase, LOCK_TIMEOUT_SECONDS (120s) elapsed\n- **Refunds**: Both players get their entry_amount back\n- **Cleanup**: Closes account, returns rent to creator\n\n#### **ForceClose** (`force_close.rs`)\n- **Requires**: Config authority (admin)\n- **Purpose**: Emergency closure for accounts that can't be deserialized (migration recovery)\n- **Action**: Drains all lamports to recipient, zeros account data\n\n---\n\n### **6. SHARED LIBRARY** (`solana/shared/src/`)\n\n#### **Constants** (`constants.rs`)\n```rust\nSIDE_HEADS = 0\nSIDE_TAILS = 1\nPHASE_WAITING = 0\nPHASE_LOCKED = 1\nPHASE_SETTLED = 2\nPHASE_CANCELLED = 3\nLOCK_TIMEOUT_SECONDS = 120\nfrom_randomness(byte) → byte % 2\nis_valid_side(side) → bool\n```\n\n#### **Tiers** (`tiers.rs`)\n```rust\nTIER_AMOUNTS[6] = [\n  5_000_000      // 0.005 SOL — Iron (tier 0)\n  10_000_000     // 0.01 SOL — Bronze (tier 1)\n  100_000_000    // 0.1 SOL — Silver (tier 2)\n  250_000_000    // 0.25 SOL — Gold (tier 3)\n  500_000_000    // 0.5 SOL — Platinum (tier 4)\n  1_000_000_000  // 1.0 SOL — Diamond (tier 5)\n]\nget_tier_amount(tier) → Result<u64>\n```\n\n#### **Fees** (`fees.rs`)\n```rust\nMAX_FEE_BPS = 1000 (safety cap, 10%)\nTOTAL_FEE_BPS = 300 (3%)\n  REVENUE_BPS = 200\n  RAKEBACK_BPS = 70\n  CHEST_BPS = 30\n\ncalculate_fee(amount) → u64\ncalculate_net_payout(pool) → (fee, net_payout)\nsplit_fee(fee) → (revenue, rakeback, chest)\n```\n\n---\n\n### **7. DEPENDENCIES**\n\n#### **Coinflip Program Cargo.toml**\n```toml\nanchor-lang = \"0.32.1\" (workspace)\nrng-shared = { path = \"../../shared\" }\nplatform = { path = \"../platform\", features = [\"cpi\"] }\nephemeral-vrf-sdk = \"0.2.3\", features = [\"anchor\"]\n\nFeatures:\n- default = [\"mock-oracle\"] (skips VRF CPI in tests)\n- cpi = [\"no-entrypoint\"] (for CPI clients)\n- idl-build = [\"anchor-lang/idl-build\"]\n```\n\n#### **Workspace Cargo.toml**\n```toml\nMembers: shared, programs/coinflip, programs/platform\n\nDependencies:\n- anchor-lang = \"0.32.1\"\n- orao-solana-vrf = \"0.7.0\" (default-features = false, features = [\"cpi\"])\n- rng-shared = { path = \"shared\" }\n- solana-sha256-hasher = \"2.3\"\n```\n\n#### **Shared Library Cargo.toml**\n```toml\nanchor-lang = \"0.32.1\" (workspace)\norao-solana-vrf = \"0.7.0\" (workspace)\nsolana-sha256-hasher = \"2.3\" (workspace)\n\nFeatures:\n- mock-vrf\n```\n\n---\n\n### **8. MATCH LIFECYCLE**\n\n```\nWAITING\n  ├─ CreateMatch: creator places bet (escrow locked)\n  │\n  └─→ JoinMatch: opponent joins (requests VRF)\n      │\n      └─→ LOCKED\n          ├─ VRF callback → ResolveMatch\n          │  └─→ SETTLED\n          │      ├─ ClaimPayout (winner + fee split)\n          │      └─ Account closed\n          │\n          └─ TimeoutCancel (if >120s)\n             └─ Both refunded, account closed\n\nOR\n\nWAITING\n  └─ CancelMatch: creator cancels before join\n     └─ Escrow + rent returned to creator\n```\n\n---\n\n### **9. KEY DESIGN PATTERNS**\n\n1. **Match PDA Seeds**: `[b\"match\", creator.key()]` — One active match per creator\n2. **Config PDA Seeds**: `[b\"coinflip_config\"]` — Global singleton\n3. **Escrow Model**: Match PDA holds both players' stakes (no separate escrow account)\n4. **VRF Integration**: \n   - Caller seed = match_key bytes (unique per match)\n   - Discriminator = hardcoded resolve_match signature\n   - Account metas passed to VRF callback\n5. **Fee Model**: Hardcoded 3%, split 200/70/30 (revenue/rakeback/chest)\n6. **Profile Updates**: CPI to platform program only if profiles exist (data_is_empty check)\n7. **Rent Handling**: Closed accounts refund rent to creator automatically (Anchor constraint)\n8. **Mock Mode**: `feature = \"mock-oracle\"` conditionally skips VRF CPI (for bankrun tests)\n\n---\n\n### **10. COMPLETE FILE LISTINGS**\n\nAll files have been read in full:\n- ✅ `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/programs/coinflip/src/state.rs`\n- ✅ `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/programs/coinflip/src/lib.rs`\n- ✅ `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/programs/coinflip/Cargo.toml`\n- ✅ `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/Cargo.toml`\n- ✅ All 8 instruction handlers (initialize_config, create_match, join_match, resolve_match, claim_payout, cancel_match, timeout_cancel, force_close)\n- ✅ Error definitions (12 error codes)\n- ✅ Shared library: constants, tiers, fees, lib.rs\n- ✅ Shared Cargo.toml"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a41cce83c02c38d30 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 46901\ntool_uses: 22\nduration_ms: 45007</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"s